history.content: IMO AI’ing is more rewarding for 61A. You actually get the chance to teach to 61a students whereas in 61b you’re mostly just walking through a debugger with students

I have been an academic intern for CS61A for a year now, and I am wondering if it's time for a change of pace. I took CS61B last spring, so I avoided it this semester because I heard of the large differences between the professors. Now that Professor Hug is teaching again, I'm thinking about switching to 61B to keep up my skills and add some variety to my schedule. Should I make the switch? Should I do both (one with units and one without)?
history.subject: Academic Intern for CS61A or B?
